name: Vintage Camping Kettle
description: This very cute vintage camping kettle is ideal for any retro outing. The kettle has a folding handle, white screw cover on spout and in overall good condition for age.

name: Vintage Flip Desk Calendar
description: We were delighted to find this vintage flip calendar on a recent trip to France.  This is a great compact desk calendar from the 1970s.  It has a simple push button mechanism for each day.  This would be a great addition to any desk or shelf.  The retro shape surrounds a simple face.

name: Vintage Roselle Midwinter Coffee Pot
description: This coffee pot is a fine example of Midwinter design and craftsmanship.  The design is delicately illustrated with vibrant colours on a pure white background.  The coffee pot is in excellent condition with no cracks, stains or fading.

name: Vintage Baby Walker with Building Blocks
description: A lovely vintage baby walker with building blocks.  This is a really lovely set in super vintage condition.  Blocks are brightly coloured in red, blue, yellow and green.

name: Vintage Figgjo Flint turi-design 'Lotte' Milk Jug
description: This milk jug is a fine example of Norwegian design and craftsmanship; made by Figgjo Flint, part of the "Lotte" line (circa 1970's).  The design is delicately illustrated with vibrant colours on a pure white background; it features a hand-painted screen print of a female wrapped in flowers.  The milk jug is in excellent condition with no cracks, stains or fading.

name: Vintage Elephant Money Box
description: This is one of our favourite items to date, a vintage money box in the form of a retro stylised elephant.  The wheel on the top can be turned to set various occasions e.g. ‘Christmas, Easter, ssh! top secret!,’ etc and the date can be entered underneath.  The money box can be free standing or fixed to the wall.  The item was made in England and is in excellent condition measuring approximately 11.2cm tall.

name: Learning by Numbers – Vintage French Number Stamps 1-10
description: This is a beautiful vintage set of number stamps 1-10.  Each number has the corresponding number of circles to colour - which makes learning much more fun and interactive.  The stamps come in the original box.

name: Telephone Music Chime and Desk Tidy
description: We are delighted to present this beautiful telephone music chime and desk tidy.  Place the telephone receiver on the black platform and your caller will hear the tune of ‘rain drops are falling on my head’ – we love it.  It also functions as a desk tidy and measures 13 x 7.5 x 7.5cm.

name: Vintage School Stamps
description: Print images with ease using this beautiful vintage school stamps.  The set contains four educational stamps in total.  Each print measures 15.3 x 12.5cm.  The handle format makes it very easy to use.

name: Vintage Map Set
description: Print maps with ease using this beautiful vintage map set.  The set contains a map of the World, UK, Europe, Asia, North and South America.  Each map print measures 16 x 12.7cm.  The wooden handle format makes it very easy to use.  We just adore this vintage set.

name: Bright Red Vintage Hand Lamp
description: This fabulous vintage battery lamp is in full working order.  It is great for taking on camping trips or to have in your home - just in case there is an electrical failure.  Supplied with battery.

name: Vintage Terraillon Weighing Scales
description:
This vintage beauty is so nicely designed that it has been a part of MOMA's collection since its release.  The scales where designed by industrial designers Marco Zanuso and Richard Sapper for Terraillon France.  It is made of sturdy, bright and beautiful yellow ABS plastic and measures approximately 16.5 x 10.5 x 11.5cm. The top flips to act as a weighing bowl, or left as a weighing platform for larger items the playful almost puzzle-like quality perfectly reflects the geometric Pop Modernism of the late 60s.

Art Historian Sylvia Katz noted this was the perfect scale for "the land of the gourmets", sleek and compact, easily stowed or displayed, and produced in bold modern colours, this elegant and logically designed kitchen scale is not only beautiful, but is also superbly functional.

name: Vintage Olivetti Box
description: This fabulous little box by Olivetti is ideal for holding paperclips and bits and bobs to keep your desk tidy.  The box measures 6 x 6 x 6cm.

name: Vintage French Desk Calendar
description: We were delighted to find this calendar on a recent trip to France.  This is a great compact desk calendar from the 1970s.  It has a simple push button mechanism for each day, date and month.  This would be a great addition to any desk or shelf.  The retro shape surrounds a simple face, while the text is in French.  The calendar measures 10.5 x 7 x 5.5cm.

name: Vintage Hole Punch by Leober
description: We found this great hole punch on a recent trip to France.  The paper size and hole punch dimension are adjustable, which is unusual for a hole punch of this age.  The punch is really heavy which makes it very sturdy for all your punching needs.

name: Vintage Insulex Food/Thermos Flask
description: This is a very fashionable red vintage camping or picnic flask.  The lid screws on and off to ensure the contents are airtight and the carry handle is very sturdy.  The flask has the original inner rubber sealing lid.  Overall the flask is in good condition.

name: Vintage Horseshoe Magnet by James Galt & Co
description: This is a traditional horseshoe magnet with its original keeper.  The magnet measures 10cm in length and comes in the original box.

name: Vintage Red Stapler
description: Organise your paperwork with this great vintage stapler. The stapler measures 11.5cm long x 3cm wide.

name: Vintage 1970's Stamp Block
description: We just love the bright 1970 graphics of this stamp block. The stamp block is in mint condition.  Pop them in a frame and they will look fab.  The block measures 15.0 cm x 9.5cm (frame not included).

name: Vintage 1967 Animal Stamp Block
description: We just love the bright 1960 graphics of this stamp block. The stamp block is in mint condition and features colourful hedgehog, a school house stove and a schoolboy with a giraffe. The block measures 14.5cm x 10.5cm (frame not included).

name: Stylish 1974 Trimphone
description:
This is an excellent original 1974 edition Trimphone in two-tone colour.  The photographs are a good representation of the actual green/blue colour.  

The dial is very smooth and the handset cable has been thoroughly cleaned with no twists.   The four rubber feet are in very good condition and the volume dial on the base is working perfectly.  Speech is good and the bell ringer is working very well.  The phone has been converted to a standard BT plug and is ready to use straight away with any landline that supports pulse dialling.

name: Vintage 1971 Beetroot Stamp Block
description: We just love the bright 1970 graphics of this stamp block.  The stamp block is in mint condition and features colourful beetroot, a waving sun and a butterfly. The block measures 14.5cm x 10cm (frame not included).

name: Vintage Guzzini Orange Plastic Trays
description: Two vintage serving trays by the Italian designer Guzzini.  Great for serving Sunday morning breakfast in bed, a stylish addition to any kitchen.  Each tray measures 46 x 28.5cm.

name: The Ladybird a.b.c
description: This is a lovely vintage ladybird picture book for children to learn their a b c’s.

name: 1960’s Carlton Ware Train Money Box
description: Chu, Chu, Chu…all pennies onboard.  This is a fantastic 1960s Carlton Ware train money box designed by Vivienne Brennen.  The numbers are bright orange on a red background.  The back is plain white and comes with the original stopper.  In excellent condition, free from chips or cracks.  Measuring 13cm high x 15cm wide and stamped on the bottom Made in England “Trade Mark”.

name: Vintage Red Plastic Lemon/Orange Squeezer
description: A bright red orange squeezer, with inset tray to catch fruit pips - perfect to brighten up any kitchen worktop.

name: Pair of Vintage Easy Stack Egg Cups
description: A pair of fabulous vintage egg cups dating back to the 1960s. They are both in excellent condition and are bright mustard yellow in colour.

name: Vintage Hammarplast Measuring Jug
description: This is a lovely olive green vintage Hammarplast measuring jug.  The jug has cup measurements on the side from 1 to 10.  This would make a great mid century modern addition to any kitchen.  The jug is in vintage condition with some surface marks to the plastic.

name: Vintage Desk Calendar
description: This is a fun, compact desk calendar from the 1970s.  It has a simple rolling mechanism for each day, date and month.  The retro shape surrounds a nice silver face with white uppercase Helvetica letters and numbers.  The calendar measures 10 x 6 x 5cm and comes with the original box.

name: Vintage Lady Braun Elegance Shaver
description: Designed in 1979 by the iconic designers Dieter Rams and Roland Ullmann this item is simple, innovative and in excellent condition.  The components match faultlessly, the colour is vibrant and the shaver functions perfectly, a fantastic item.

name: Words we need for Numbers
description: This is a lovely 1966 ladybird reading book teaching children those words used most frequently in situations involving numbers.  The words are linked with illstrations to aid learning.

name: Vintage Cup/Soup Bowl
description: This lovely vintage item has a simple design in a deep blue and is stamped on the base ‘ENGLAND MADE’.  The handle is very unusual, this would make a lovely little storage bowl.  The item is in good condition.

name: Magnifying Glass by Coil
description: Ideal for inspecting your stamp collection, this original vintage 1960s coil hand magnifier measures 22.5 cm in length.  The casing is cream plastic and the lens measures 10 x 7.5cm.

name: Vintage French Educational Stamps
description: This is a great set of vintage rubber stamps by Fernand Nathan.  The set comprises of ten stamps in total and comes in the original box.  Each stamp measures 3.5cm x 4.5cm.

name: Vintage Stelton Jug
description: Designed in 1977 by Erik Magnussen this item is today a design icon with the unique rocker stopper.  Stamped on the base Stelton, Design: Erik Magnussen, made in Denmark.  Due to the age of the item there is some wear on the exterior of the jug.

name: Vintage Wooden Picture Cubes
description: This beautiful little puzzle comprises of four cubes, which make up six different little images.  The overall size of the puzzle measures 7.5 x 7.5cm.

name: Vintage Set of Arklow Studio Kraft Cups
description: We love the simple retro design and bright colours of this set.  The set includes three cups and saucers - all in very good condition.

name: Vintage Ladybird Book - Wizard of Oz
description: This is a lovely vintage ladybird ‘read it your self’ level 4 reading book.  Familiar fairytales and exciting stories will amuse children and encourage them to progress and become confident readers.

name: Vintage Ladybird Book - The Pied Piper of Hamelin
description: This is a lovely vintage ladybird ‘read it your self’ level 4 reading book.  Familiar fairytales and exciting stories will amuse children and encourage children to progress and become confident readers.

name: Vintage Floral Plates by John Russell
description: Four pretty floral print plates in autumn shades of brown, yellow and green. The plates measure 17.5cm in diameter and are free from chips and cracks.  Stamped of the back ‘Camelot’.

name: GPO Dial Telephone
description:
This is a beautiful cream original GPO dial telephone (8746G) in full working order.

The phone is in great condition - the dial is very smooth and the handset cable has no twists.   The four rubber feet are in very good condition.  Speech is good and the bell ringer is working very well.  The phone has been converted to a standard BT plug and is ready to use straight away with any landline that supports pulse dialling.

name: Little Kermode the Vintage Chiltern Mohair Bear
description: Little Kermode’s habitat is under threat and he needs a new home.  He measures 15cm in height and is very easy to look after – he just needs one hug each day.

name: Vintage 1950’s Atomic Plant Stands
description: We think these 1950’s plant stands are fabulous and they also make excellent umbrella stands.  Made from plastic weave on a metal frame they would look great in any room.  Both stands are in good condition with some wear to the rubber, measuring 25cm high x 21cm in diameter.  Choose from white or bright turquoise.

name: Four ‘Little House’ Series of Books
description: These four beautiful books written by Laura Ingalls Wilder are widely known and loved as the ‘Little House’ series of books.  The set was reprinted in the 1970’s and includes, On the Banks of Plum Creek, Little House on the Prairie, These Happy Golden Years and Little Town on the Prairie.  Laura Elizabeth Ingalls Wilder was an American author who wrote these books based on her own childhood.

name: Three Hornsea Saffron Jars
description: Three lovely 1970’s Hornsea jars for cinnamon, spice and all things nice.  Each jar measures 7cm tall x 5cm diameter – in good condition and stamped on the base ‘Hornsea, England 1972, Saffron’.

name: Adorable Espresso Cups
description: These are the cutest little cups.  The design is very simple with vibrant colours of orange, blue and green.  The cups are in very good condition and are free from any crazing, cracks or chips.

name: Vintage Glass Jelly Mould
description: This is a lovely vintage oval jelly mould, ideal for making wobbly jelly.  The mould measures 13.5cm long and 9cm and is in very good clean condition with no chips or cracks.

name: Vintage Coffee Pot, Jug and Saucers
description:
This vintage Elizabethan coffee set dates from the 1960’s and is decorated with a fabulous flower design in purple and pink on a pure white background. The set comprises a coffee pot, milk jug and six saucers.

The set is in excellent condition except for a chip on the spout of the milk jug.

name: Vintage Salt and Pepper Set
description: This little salt and pepper set is adorable, measuring only 3.6cm tall these would make a fantastic addition to any picnic set.

name: Vintage EVER READY Spotlight Bulbs
description: This is a superb complete set of fifty EVER READY spotlight bulbs, in the original box.  These bulbs would have been used in old bicycle lanterns.  This is a great vintage item to add to any collection.

name: Vintage Tinplate Kitchen Set
description: This is a beautiful little vintage toy kitchen.  The complete set includes four appliances - a white fridge with opening door and shelves, a blue stove with opening door, a green sink with a cupboard below and a cream washing machine with opening lid and spinner.  The set is in good condition for its age and comes with the original box.

name: The Dead Sea Scrolls by J. M. Allegro
description: The Dead Sea Scrolls written by J. M. Allegro was first published in 1956 this edition was reprinted in 1957.  In 1947 an Arab shepherd stumbled upon a cave near the Dead Sea containing seven ancient scrolls.  They proved to be part of the library of a Jewish monastic community living before and during the time of Christ.  The author John Marco Allegro was asked to fly to Jerusalem to join the international Scrolls team.  This book is a study of the archaeological material from the Dead Sea.  The book is good condition for its age.

name: Vintage Hornsea 'Saffron' Cups
description: Two lovely Hornsea cups in the Saffron design, produced by Hornsea through the 1970's and is now a very collectable pattern.  Both cups are in good condition with no chips, cracks or fading.

name: Mrs Ram the Vintage Sheep
description: Mrs Ram comes from an old family of Merino sheep and is prized for her beautiful wool.  She is a very gentle sheep and would like to go into retirement and join a family who can look after her in her old age. Overall Mrs Ram measures 33cm in height.

name: 1975 Hornsea Storage Jar
description:
Lovely Hornsea storage jar, England 1975 in Saffron pattern.

The Saffron design was produced by Hornsea through the 1970's and is now a very collectable pattern.  The jar is unmarked, leaving you free to store what you wish.

name: The Merchant of Venice and All’s Well That Ends Well by William Shakespeare
description:
The Merchant of Venice (reprinted in 1981) and All’s Well That Ends Well (reprinted in 1984) published by Penguin books - the front covers have been beautifully illustrated.

The Merchant of Venice is a tragic comedy by William Shakespeare, believed to have been written between 1596 and 1598.

All’s Well That Ends Well was originally classified as one of Shakespeare's comedies, the play is now considered by some critics to be one of his problem plays, so named because they cannot be neatly classified as tragedy or comedy.

Both books are in good condition.

name: Vintage Dolls
description: Two vintage dolls, excellent for displaying together, the dolls have enjoyed a playful life and this is reflected in the condition.

name: A Guide to English Schools by Tyrrell Burgess
description: A Guide to English Schools written by Tyrrell Burgess was first published in 1964, this edition was reprinted in 1975.  The author, journalist and academic Tyrrell Burgess, was a radically innovative thinker and educational practitioner.  In 1964 this book was a ‘straightforward and up-to-date guide to schools of all kinds in England and Wales’.  The book is good condition for its age.

name: Polaroid 635CL Supercolor Vintage Camera
description: This camera is compact, stylish, and would be a great addition to any collection.  This Polaroid film camera accepts the 600 Land film and is in full working order, tested with old film.  The built-in automatic flash fires a high-intensity burst of light when shooting in low-light conditions.  The close-up lens button on the Polaroid Supercolor 635 CL lets you switch to close-up photography in an instant.  The camera comes with the original box and instruction manual.

name: The Grim Smile of the Five Towns by Arnold Bennett
description: The Grim Smile of the Five Towns written by Arnold Bennett was first published in 1907 this edition was reissued in 1971.  The author Arnold Bennett was born in 1867 in the ‘Potteries’ – the region of England about which almost all his best novels were written.  The book is good condition for its age.

name: Vintage Staffordshire Serving Platter and Jug
description: This is a pretty Staffordshire serving platter and jug, with a pretty floral print in shades of brown and turquoise on a pure white background.  The oval serving platter measures 23.3cm wide x 31cm long and the jug measures 7.3cm high x 11.3cm in diameter.  Both items are in good condition with no cracks, stains or fading.

name: Vintage John TAMS ltd. Cup and Saucer
description: This is a lovely vintage cup and saucer with floral design. The cup and saucer are in good condition with no chips, but the glaze is a little cracked to the internal surface of the cup as often happens with ceramics of this age.

name: Vintage Floral Barker Bros "Royalty" Plates
description: Two pretty Barker Bros "Royalty" floral print plates in shades of purple, green and blue. The plates measure 20.5cm in diameter.  Both plates are free from chips and cracks.

name: Britvil Vintage Swizzle Sticks
description: This fabulous set of vintage swizzle sticks would be an ideal addition to any vintage soiree.  The swizzle sticks are in excellent unused condition, with a list of suggested cocktail recipes on the back of the card.

name: Vintage Randwyck MAASTRICHT HOLLAND Coffee Set
description: This is a complete set of four glass coffee cups with matching coffee jug and tray.  The set is in excellent unused condition.

name: Bright Red Vintage Desk Tidy
description: This is an excellent bright red vintage desk tidy with four drawers to store all the bits and bobs, keeping your desk clutter free and tidy.  There is also a very useful pen and pencil holder.  Overall the desk tidy measures 12cm high x 8cm wide.

name: 1960s Arabia Finland 'Orange Sections' Marmalade Pot by Raija Uosikkinen
description: Fabulous piece of retro Scandinavian ceramics from the famous Finnish manufacturer, Arabia, and in the highly sought after marmalade pot - which was in production from 1965-1975.  Designed by Raija Uosikkinen, it repetitive orange pattern is very desirable on a white ground and is marked to the base with 'Arabia Made in Finland 2-68'.  In excellent condition with no cracks, stains or fading.

name: Vintage 1972 Munich Olympic Stamps
description: We just love the bright 1970 graphics of these Olympic stamps.  Ideal for starting a new stamp collection or adding to any existing collection.  Just choose you’re favourite (frame not included).

name: Vintage Copal Flip Clock
description:
In 1967, Copal, a Japanese precision mechanism company released this stylish flip clock. This green flip clock is in excellent condition and is a great addition to any room. The clock features a barbershop spinning mechanism which works perfectly.  The clock measures 13cm long x 7.5cm wide.

Was £70.00 - Now £55.00

name: Vintage Figgjo Flint Turi-design 'Lotte' Tea Cups and Saucers
description: Two beautiful vintage Figgjo Flint ‘Lotte’ tea cups and saucers - the design is delicately illustrated with vibrant colours on a pure white background.  This is a fine example of Norwegian design and craftsmanship.  Both cups are in excellent condition with no cracks, stains or fading.

name: Vintage Figgjo Flint turi-design 'Lotte' Coffee Pot
description:
This coffee pot is a fine example of Norwegian design and craftsmanship; made by Figgjo Flint, part of the "Lotte" line (circa 1970's).  The design is delicately illustrated with vibrant colours on a pure white background; it features a hand-painted screen print of a female wrapped in flowers on both sides of the coffee pot.  The coffee pot is in excellent condition with no cracks, stains or fading.

Was £45.00 - Now £40.00

name: Jens H Quistgaard 'Kobenstyle' Yellow Enamelled Pitcher
description:
A beautiful yellow enamelled Dansk Kobenstyle pitcher with a rattan wrapped handle, designed by Jens Quistgaard's.  This pitcher circa 1955 for Dansk Designs is one of the earlier Danish made pieces marked on the base with Dansk's "four ducks" logo, the initials "IHQ" are Jens Quistgaard's mark.  The pitcher measures 20cm high and in good condition, one small nick to base of handle otherwise stunning.

Was £95.00 - Now £85.00

name: PIFCO Vintage Hand Lamp
description:
This is a superb 1970’s PIFCO hand lamp in excellent condition.  The lamp is like new, the orange colour is vibrant and the large brown rubber button is in great condition, this is a great object and would brighten up any shelf.

Was £8.00 - Now £6.00

name: Six Small Vintage Jelly Moulds
description:
This is a beautiful set of six vintage aluminium jelly moulds.  They are in good condition and have a lovely flower design.

Was £6.00 - Now £4.00

name: Vintage Figgjo Flint Turi-design 'Daisy' Plate
description: This is a pretty Figgjo Flint ‘Daisy’ plate with vibrant colours on a pure white background.  This is a fine example of Norwegian design.  The plate measures 20cm in diameter and us in good condition with no cracks, stains or fading, however there is a slight surface mark as shown in the photographs.

name: Large Cathrineholm Lotus Pot
description:
Large vintage avocado green enamel lotus pot by Cathrineholm.  A great addition to any mid-century modern kitchen, for cooking or display.  Stamped on the base – Cathrineholm made in Norway.

Overall this item is in great condition, with only minor chips at the base of the exterior and a chip to one of the handles.  Measuring 16cm deep x 24cm in diameter.

Was £80.00 - Now £65.00.

name: Sugar Bowl by THOMAS Germany
description:
This pretty sugar bowl by Thomas pottery has a very colourful pattern in pink and purple on a white background.  The sugar bowl is in excellent condition free from chips and cracks.

Was £15.00 - Now £10.00

name: Vintage Teak Mouse
description: Cute little teak wooden mouse, circa 1960s with definite mid century style.  The mouse has a painted nose, bead eyes and felt ears.  The mouse is 5.5cm long (14cm long with tail).

name: Arabia Finland Bee Honey Pot by Raija Uosikkinen
description:
Fabulous piece of retro Scandinavian ceramics from the famous Finnish manufacturer, Arabia, in the highly sought after 'Bee' design - which was in production from 1965-1975.  Designed by Raija Uosikkinen, it repetitive bee pattern is very desirable on a white background and is marked to the base with 'Arabia Made in Finland 1-66'.  Bee Honey Pot is without the original lid.

Was £45.00 - Now £35.00

name: Six Vintage Fondue Forks
description:
This is a complete set of six brightly coloured fondue forks.  The stainless steel forks are in really good condition for their age and come with the original box (the Harrods price tag is still on the box).      

Was £6.00 - Now £4.00

name: Mustard Pot by Lord Nelson Pottery
description: This vintage Mustard Pot by Lord Nelson Pottery has a very beautiful vintage pattern. The colours are bright and typical of the Gaytime pattern.  The pot is in excellent condition and is marked to the base ‘Lord Nelson Pottery, Gaytime’.

name: Vintage Child’s Chair
description: This is a sweet little vintage child’s plywood chair, and would look great in any nursery or playroom.  The chair shows signs of age and wear as shown in the photographs.

name: Vintage Easy Stack Egg Cups
description: This fabulous set of six vintage Arthur Douglas egg cups date back to the 1960s.  They are all in excellent unused condition with the original box.  Each egg cup is marked regd design 899085 made in England.

name: Two Vintage JAJ Pyrex DRINKUPS
description: Two stylish grey Pyrex DRINKUPS tea/coffee cups, in good condition, without chips, cracks or any damage.  Both cups are marked on the base JAJ, Made in England.

name: Vintage Cuisenaire Set
description: This Cuisenaire set was invented by the Belgian primary school teacher Georges Cuisenaire - the coloured rods have long been helping children learn maths.
